Radebe - popularly known as Vusi on the soapie 'Backstage' - was diagnosed with cancer in 2018 and had been undergoing treatment since last year. JOHANNESBURG - South African actor Sibusiso Radebe has reportedly passed away. Radebe - popularly known as Vusi on the soapie Backstage - was diagnosed with cancer in 2018 and had been undergoing treatment since last year. Fans and fellow actors have been sending condolences on social media today.